                        "name": "Black Seed Cloud",
                        "type": "offensive_action",
                        "text": "The counteflora releases a cloud of black seedpods in a 15-foot-radius emanation. Non-counteflora creatures in the area must succeed at a Fortitude save or breathe in the toxic seeds. (Against plants and fungi, the seeds burrow into the creatures\u2019 flesh rather than infiltrate their lungs.)<br/> <b>Counteflora Toxin</b> (<a aonid=\"37\" game-obj=\"Traits\">contact</a> [for plants and fungi] or <a aonid=\"96\" game-obj=\"Traits\">inhaled</a>, <a aonid=\"126\" game-obj=\"Traits\">poison</a>) <b>Saving Throw</b> DC 30 Fortitude (DC 32 for plants and fungi); <b>Maximum Duration</b> 6 rounds; <b>Stage 1</b> 4d6 poison damage and <a aonid=\"13\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">enfeebled</a> 1 (1 round); <b>Stage 2</b> 6d6 poison damage, enfeebled 1, and <a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">fascinated</a> (1 round)",
